Changing Home & Respawn location.
Difficulty - Basic
Tired of having the same old home as everyone else ? want something unique you can customize & have some fun with ? then follow these simple steps.
Step 1 - Open your server folder, goto source\server
Step 2 - Open config.java
Step 3 - Press ctrl & f at the same time on your keyboard
Step 4 - Search start
Step 5 - You should see these 2 lines.
[code]public static final int START_LOCATION_X = 3087; 
public static final int START_LOCATION_Y = 3496;[/code]
Step 6 - Change the 4 digit number ids to your desired location, you can find your location by typing ::mypos, dont have that command ? look further in this tutorial on adding it. " 3087, 3496 is edgeville "
Step 7 - Below your start statements you should see respawn, the same applies, change the coordinates where you want to respawn when you die, example " 3222, 3218 " is lumbridge.
Step 8 - Save,Compile and your done.

Adding objects.
Difficulty - Easy
Alright adding objects is a simple thing to do, but it can get confusing when your first looking at a bunch of numbers and brackets, well ill help you begin to understand how things work.[/color]
Step 1 -Get your object ids [url=http://pastebin.com/8neYCBBj]http://pastebin.com/8neYCBBj[/url]
Step 2 -Open your server folder, source>server>world, open objectManager.java
Step 3 -Now scroll down until you see statements like this, [code]		c.getPA().checkObjectSpawn(409, 3238, 9315, 3, 10);[/code]
This a prayer altar but lets not worry about that. Now press enter to start a new line and ill explain this code.
Alright, basically what this is saying, is getPA " player assistant " check this spawn, (objectID, XCoord, YCoord, Direction, 10);
Once you've added your object, save & compile.

Adding a master-reset command.
Difficulty - Easy
Alright the purpose of this command is to allow you to reset all your skills back to 1, if desired. rather then using ::resetskill, this is pretty much only if you want a clean slate.

Step 1 -Open up your server folder source>server>models>players>packets, open command.java
Step 2 -Search for [code] c.playerLevel[i] = 99;[/code]

[code]c.getPA().requestUpdates();
}[/code]
^ Under this last bracket press enter and paste this.
[code]		if (playerCommand.equalsIgnoreCase("MasterReset")) { // what this does is check if the command is exactly as I wrote it, if it's 1 char off, it won't work. 
				for (int i = 0; i < 24; i++) {
					c.playerLevel[i] = 1;
					c.playerXP[i] = c.getPA().getXPForLevel(1);
					c.getPA().refreshSkill(i);
					c.sendMessage("Skills reset");
				}
					c.getPA().requestUpdates();
			}

    		}[/code]
